%N A386849 For n >= 0, a(n) is the least t >= 1 such that n^2 + 8*t is a square (A000290) where t is a triangular number (A000217) or a(n) = -1 if no such t exists.
%C A386849 The two solutions of the Diophantine equation x^2 + n*x - 2*t = 0 are x_1 = ( - n + sqrt(n^2 + 8*t)) / 2 and x_2 = ( - n - sqrt(n^2 + 8*t)) / 2.
%C A386849 a(n) <= n^4/32 - n^2/8, with equality if n is in A014574. - _Robert Israel_, Sep 21 2025
%H A386849 Ctibor O. Zizka, <a href="/A386849/a386849_1.png">Plot of n vs. a(n)</a>
%F A386849 It appears that a(2*n+3) = A000217(A082183(n+1)). - _Michel Marcus_, Sep 22 2025
%e A386849 For n = 4, the least triangular number t >= 1 such that (16 + 8*t) is a square is t = 6, thus a(4) = 6.
%p A386849 f:= proc(n) local s, S,q;
%p A386849   q:= n^2-1;
%p A386849   S:= select(t -> t - q/t mod 4 = 2, numtheory:-divisors(q));
%p A386849   S:= select (`>=`, map(s -> (s-q/s)/4-1/2,S),1);
%p A386849   if S = {} then return -1 fi;
%p A386849   s:= min(S);
%p A386849   s*(s+1)/2
%p A386849 end proc:
%p A386849 f(1):= 1:
%p A386849 map(f,[$0..100]); # _Robert Israel_, Sep 21 2025
%t A386849 a[n_] := Module[{k = 1, t = 1}, While[! IntegerQ[Sqrt[n^2 + 8*t]], k++; t += k]; t]; a[0] = a[2] = a[3] = -1; Array[a, 100, 0] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Sep 21 2025 *)
%o A386849 (PARI) a(n) = if ((n==0) || (n==2) || (n==3), -1, my(k=1); while (!issquare(n^2+4*k*(k+1)), k++); t=k*(k+1)/2); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Sep 21 2025
